": "//lccn.loc.gov/sn92053241/marcxml"}], "other_title": ["Publisher's box: Free trader-journal,", "Publisher's box: Free trader-journal and fair dealer,", "Ottawa free trader-journal", "Ottawa free trader", "Ottawa journal", "Free trader journal and Ottawa fair dealer", "Free trader journal", "Free trader journal and fair dealer", "Ottawa free trader journal"], "partof": [{"count": 862, "title": "free trader-journal and ottawa fair dealer (ottawa, ill.) 1920-1927", "url": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=partof:free+trader-journal+and+ottawa+fair+dealer+%28ottawa,+ill.%29+1920-1927&fo=json"}, {"count": 3203926, "title": "chronicling america", "url": "https://www.loc.gov/collections/chronicling-america/?fo=json"}, {"count": 3225157, "title": "serial and government publications division", "url": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=partof:serial+and+government+publications+division&fo=json"}], "partof_collection": ["chronicling america"], "partof_division": ["serial and government publications division"], "partof_title": ["free trader-journal and ottawa fair dealer (ottawa, ill.) 1920-1927"], "place_of_publication": "Ottawa, Ill.", "publication_frequency": ["daily"], "raw_lccn": "sn 92053241 ", "reel_numbers": ["00295873383"], "resources": [{"files": 8, "image": "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:iune:batch_iune_issue_ver01:data:sn92053241:00295873383:1921011201:0071/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg", "url": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/sn92053241/1921-01-12/ed-1/", "word_coordinates": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service"}], "rights": ["<p>The Library of Congress believes that the newspapers in Chronicling America are in the public domain or have no known copyright restrictions.  Newspapers published in the United States more than 95 years ago are in the public domain in their entirety. Any newspapers in Chronicling America that were published less than 95 years ago are also believed to be in the public domain, but may contain some copyrighted third party materials. Researchers using newspapers published less than 95 years ago should be alert for modern content (for example, registered and renewed for copyright and published with notice) that may be copyrighted.  Responsibility for making an independent legal assessment of an item and securing any necessary permissions ultimately rests with persons desiring to use the item.</p>\n<p>The NEH awardee responsible for producing each digital object is presented in the Chronicling America page display, below the page image  \u2013 e.g. Image produced by the Library of Congress. For more information on current NDNP awardees, see <a href=\"https://www.loc.gov/ndnp/listawardees.html\">https://www.loc.gov/ndnp/listawardees.html</a>.</p>\n<p>For more information on Library of Congress policies and disclaimers regarding rights and reproductions, see <a href=\"https://www.loc.gov/homepage/legal.html\">https://www.loc.gov/homepage/legal.html</a></p>"], "score": 14.141635, "shard": "05", "shelf_id": "sn92053241, 1921-01-12, Edition 1", "site": ["chroniclingamerica"], "source_group": "ndnp/iune", "source_modified": "2000-01-01T12:00:00Z", "subject": ["newspapers", "la salle county", "ottawa (ill.)", "ottawa", "united states", "illinois"], "subject_headings": ["Ottawa (Ill.)--Newspapers", "Illinois--Ottawa", "United States--Illinois--La Salle County--Ottawa"], "subjects": [{"illinois": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:illinois&fo=json"}, {"la salle county": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:la+salle+county&fo=json"}, {"newspapers": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:newspapers&fo=json"}, {"ottawa": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:ottawa&fo=json"}, {"ottawa (ill.)": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:ottawa+%28ill.%29&fo=json"}, {"united states": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:united+states&fo=json"}], "timestamp": "2025-05-22T11:54:59.067Z", "title": "Free trader-journal and Ottawa fair dealer (Ottawa, Ill.), January 12, 1921", "type": ["issue"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/sn92053241/1921-01-12/ed-1/"}, "locations": null, "method": "mets_filesec", "more_like_this": [{"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/sn92053241/", "http://lccn.loc.gov/sn92053241"], "batch": ["iune_headline_ver02"], "campaigns": [], "date": "1920", "description": ["Daily (except Sunday and federal holidays) Vol. 4, no. 66 (Mar. 8, 1920)-v. 10, no. 36 (Jan. 5, 1927). Irregular number of pages published per issue. On Mondays, issues for Jan. 3-July 10, 1922 and July 24, 1922 include sections labeled \"Automobile Section,\" published \"for the motoring public.\" Issues for Oct. 10-17, 1921 and Mar. 6, 1922-<Dec. 30, 1922> contain various edition labels: 3 O'Clock; 4 O'Clock. Issue for Oct. 11, 1922 called also: \"Fall Festival Edition.\" Continues the numbering of Free trader-journal (Ottawa, Ill.). Various incorrect chronological, volume, issue, and page numbering designations. Available on microfilm; University Microfilms International. Archived issues are available in digital format from the Library of Congress Chronicling America online collection. Formed by the union of: Free trader-journal (Ottawa, Ill.) and: Ottawa fair dealer. Daily Republican-times (Ottawa, Ill.) (DLC)sn 92053181 (OCoLC)25758176"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-06-05T18:25:14.592Z", "group": ["newspaper-titles", "ndnp/newspapers", "catalog-split-11", "catalog", "united-states-newspaper-directory", "main-catalog-split-11"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/sn92053241/", "image_url": [], "index": 8, "language": ["english"], "latlong": [41.352103, -88.841193], "location": ["united states", "la salle county", "illinois", "ottawa"], "location_str": "", "lonlat": [-88.841193, 41.352103], "number": ["microfilm master", "online resource", "2381-3911", "25758451", "1", "microfilm service copy", "sn92053195", "2025-05-12t17:27:14.722511", "http://www.loc.gov/item/sn92053241/1922-12-30/ed-1/", "sn92053241", "univ of chicago", "2026-04-13t21:30:13", "la salle cnty libr", "original", "sn92053181", "http://www.loc.gov/item/sn92053241/1920-03-08/ed-1/", "sn92053240", "2025-06-25t14:25:09", "861", "abraham lincoln presidential libr"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "other_title": ["Publisher's box: Free trader-journal,", "Publisher's box: Free trader-journal and fair dealer,", "Ottawa free trader-journal", "Ottawa free trader", "Ottawa journal", "Free trader journal and Ottawa fair dealer", "Free trader journal", "Free trader journal and fair dealer", "Ottawa free trader journal"], "partof": ["catalog", "chronicling america", "serial and government publications division", "free trader-journal and ottawa fair dealer (ottawa, ill.) 1920-1927", "directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries"], "publication_frequency": ["daily"], "score": 56.591473, "shelf_id": "Newspaper", "site": ["chroniclingamerica", "usnd", "catalog"], "subject": ["newspapers", "la salle county", "ottawa (ill.)", "ottawa", "united states", "illinois"], "timestamp": "2026-07-18T09:33:03.460Z", "title": "Free trader-journal and Ottawa fair dealer", "type": ["title"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/sn92053241/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/2013218761/"], "campaigns": [], "date": "1841", "dates": ["[1841 TO 1843]"], "description": ["Weekly (except last week in May) Began with v. II, no. 2 (June 4, 1841); ceased with vol. IV, no. 15 (Sept. 29, 1843). Continues the numbering of Illinois free trader. Has occasional supplements. Also issued on microfilm from Bell & Howell, Micro Photo Division. Print version record. Vol. IV, no. 15 (September 29, 1843) (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed Apr. 24, 2013). Ottawa free trader (Online) 2328-6008 (DLC) 2013218762 (OCoLC)840686573"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-05-19T21:37:20.215Z", "group": ["ndnp/newspapers", "united-states-newspaper-directory"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2013218761/", "image_url": [], "index": 9, "language": ["english"], "location": ["la salle county", "ottawa", "la salle", "united states", "illinois"], "number": ["online resource", "840680059", "2013218761", "2328-5958", "2013218762", "2026-04-13t21:30:13"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "other_title": ["Illinois free trader", "Publisher's box: Free trader"], "partof": ["directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries", "the illinois free trader and lasalle county commercial advertiser (ottawa, illinois.;ottawa, ill.) 1841-1843 [online resource]", "serial and government publications division"], "publication_frequency": ["weekly"], "score": 47.3842, "shelf_id": "ISSN RECORD", "site": ["usnd"], "subject": ["newspapers", "la salle county (ill.)", "la salle county", "ottawa (ill.)", "ottawa", "la salle", "united states", "illinois"], "timestamp": "2026-05-26T20:48:08.077Z", "title": "The Illinois free trader and LaSalle County commercial advertiser", "type": ["title"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2013218761/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/2013218762/"], "campaigns": [], "date": "1843", "dates": ["[1843 TO 1916]"], "description": ["Weekly, Nov. 11, 1882-<Dec. 25, 1914> Began with vol. IV, no. 16 (Oct. 6, 1843); ceased in Nov. 1916. June 26, 1845 and June 11, 1849 are Extra issues. Continues the numbering of Illinois free trader and LaSalle County commercial advertiser. Various incorrect chronological, vol., issue, and page designation. Not published Dec. 22, 1848 or June 8, 1849. Has occasional supplements. Also issued on microfilm; Micro Photo, Inc., Cleveland, Ohio. Daily ed.: Ottawa free trader (Ottawa, Ill. : Daily), Oct. 15, 1889-Nov. 12, 1916. Merged with: La Salle County journal, to form: Weekly free trader-journal. Print version record. Vol. 52, no. 52 (August 2, 1890) (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed Apr. 24, 2013). Salle County journal (Online) Weekly free trader-journal (Online)"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-05-19T21:37:20.215Z", "group": ["ndnp/newspapers", "united-states-newspaper-directory"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2013218762/", "image_url": [], "index": 10, "language": ["english"], "location": ["la salle county", "ottawa", "la salle", "united states", "illinois"], "number": ["2328-6008", "online resource", "840686573", "2013218761", "2013218762", "2026-04-13t21:30:13"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "other_title": ["Publisher's box: Free trader,"], "partof": ["directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries", "the ottawa free trader (ottawa, illinois;ottawa, ill.) 1843-1916 [online resource]", "serial and government publications division"], "publication_frequency": ["weekly"], "score": 47.3842, "shelf_id": "ISSN RECORD", "site": ["usnd"], "subject": ["newspapers", "la salle county (ill.)", "la salle county", "ottawa (ill.)", "ottawa", "la salle", "united states", "illinois"], "timestamp": "2026-05-26T20:48:08.077Z", "title": "The Ottawa free trader", "type": ["title"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2013218762/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/2015218899/"], "campaigns": [], "date": "1920", "dates": ["[1920 TO 1927]"], "description": ["Daily (except Sunday and federal holidays) Began wiht volume 4, no. 66 (March 8, 1920); ceased January 5, 1927. Irregular number of pages published per issue. On Mondays, issues for Jan. 3-July 10, 1922 and July 24, 1922 include sections labeled \"Automobile Section,\" published \"for the motoring public.\" Issues for Oct. 10-17, 1921 and Mar. 6, 1922-<Dec. 30, 1922> contain various edition labels: 3 O'Clock; 4 O'Clock. Issue for Oct. 11, 1922 called also: \"Fall Festival Edition.\" Continues the numbering of Free trader-journal (Ottawa, Ill.). Various incorrect chronological, volume, issue, and page numbering designations. Available on microfilm; University Microfilms International. Formed by the union of: Free trader-journal (Ottawa, Ill.) and: Ottawa fair dealer. Description based on: Volume 4, no. 66 (March 8, 1920); title from masthead (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed October 14, 2015). Latest issue consulted: Vol. seven, no. 40 (December 30, 1922) (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed October 14, 2015). Daily Republican-times (Ottawa, Ill.)"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-05-19T21:37:32.598Z", "group": ["ndnp/newspapers", "united-states-newspaper-directory"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2015218899/", "image_url": [], "index": 11, "language": ["english"], "location": ["united states", "la salle county", "illinois", "ottawa"], "number": ["online resource", "sn92053195", "2381-392x", "2015218899", "924202619", "2026-04-13t21:30:13"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "other_title": ["Publisher's box: Free trader-journal,", "Publisher's box: Free trader-journal and fair dealer,", "Ottawa free trader-journal", "Ottawa free trader", "Ottawa journal", "Free trader journal and Ottawa fair dealer", "Free trader journal", "Free trader journal and fair dealer", "Ottawa free trader journal"], "partof": ["directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries", "free trader-journal and ottawa fair dealer (ottawa, illinois) 1920-1927 [online resource]", "serial and government publications division"], "publication_frequency": ["daily"], "score": 47.3842, "shelf_id": "ISSN RECORD", "site": ["usnd"], "subject": ["newspapers", "la salle county", "ottawa (ill.)", "ottawa", "united states", "illinois"], "timestamp": "2026-05-26T20:52:06.072Z", "title": "Free trader-journal and Ottawa fair dealer", "type": ["title"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2015218899/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/sn84038582/", "http://lccn.loc.gov/sn84038582"], "batch": ["iune_bibliography_ver01"], "campaigns": [], "contributor": ["delano, alonzo"], "date": "1843", "description": ["Weekly, Nov. 11, 1882-<Dec. 25, 1914> Vol. 4, no. 16 (Oct. 6, 1843)- Ceased in Nov. 1916. \"Our country -- her commerce -- and her free institutions.\" June 20, 1845 is an Extra issue and lacks numbering. Not published Dec. 22, 1848. Various incorrect chronological, vol., issue, and page numbering designation. Has occasional supplements. Also issued on microfilm; Micro Photo, Inc., Cleveland, Ohio. Archived issues are available in digital format as part of the Library of Congress Chronicling America online collection. Daily ed.: Ottawa free trader (Ottawa, Ill. : Daily), Oct. 15, 1889-Nov. 12, 1916. Merged with: La Salle County journal, to form: Weekly free trader-journal. Latest issue consulted: Dec. 25, 1914. Salle County journal (DLC)sn 92053190 (OCoLC)25756824 Weekly free trader-journal (DLC)sn 92053238 (OCoLC)25756957"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-06-05T18:25:14.142Z", "group": ["newspaper-titles", "ndnp/newspapers", "catalog-split-07", "catalog", "united-states-newspaper-directory", "main-catalog-split-07"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/sn84038582/", "image_url": [], "index": 12, "language": ["english"], "latlong": [41.352103, -88.841193], "location": ["united states", "la salle county", "illinois", "ottawa"], "location_str": "", "lonlat": [-88.841193, 41.352103], "number": ["southern illinois univ", "microfilm master", "sn92053239", "online resource", "abraham lincoln presidential libr", "illinois state univ", "sn84038582", "1", "microfilm service copy", "sn92053238", "chicago hist soc libr", "http://www.loc.gov/item/sn84038582/1890-08-02/ed-1/", "11347496", "new york hist soc, newsp proj", "sn82014968", "2025-05-12t17:27:14.722511", "american antiquarian soc, newsp proj", "univ of chicago", "dekalb cnty libr", "2025-06-25t14:22:48", "la salle cnty libr", "2328-5990", "original", "2327", "http://www.loc.gov/item/sn84038582/1843-10-06/ed-1/", "sn92053190", "2026-04-13t21:30:13"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "other_title": ["Publisher's box: Free trader,"], "partof": ["catalog", "chronicling